solution:
You have an error in RestController annotation definition. According to the docs it is:

public @interface RestController {

/**      * The value may indicate a suggestion for a logical component
  name,      * to be turned into a Spring bean in case of an autodetected
  component.     * @return the suggested component name, if any      * @since
  4.0.1      */     String value() default "";

}

Which means the value you have entered ("/backoffice/tags") is NAME of the controller not the path under which it is available. 

Add 
@RequestMapping("/backoffice/tags")
 on the controller's class and remove value from the 
@RestController
 annotation.

